Title: The Choice of Prices vs. Quantities under Uncertainty
Abstract: If duopolistic firms can choose their strategy variable, uncertainty
about demand conditions and the degree of substitutability have countervailing
effects on variable choice. High uncertainty favors prices,
while close substitutability favors quantities. For intermediate values,
a hybrid equilibrium exists.
